There is method [expect.assertions(number)][1] which verifies that a certain number of assertions are called during a test.


So you can modify test like this:
```lang=js
it(&#39;should fail but value is never emitted&#39;, () =&gt; {
  expect.assertions(1);
  someFunction().subscribe(v =&gt; expect(v).toBe(1));
});
```

  [1]: https://jestjs.io/docs/en/expect#expectassertionsnumber

